TITLE: Basic $inspect Usage in Svelte
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates basic usage of $inspect rune for logging reactive state changes. Shows monitoring of multiple state variables that update through user interactions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/blob/main/documentation/docs/02-runes/07-$inspect.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: svelte
CODE:
```
<script>
	let count = $state(0);
	let message = $state('hello');

	$inspect(count, message); // will console.log when `count` or `message` change
</script>

<button onclick={() => count++}>Increment</button>
<input bind:value={message} />
```

